findings.remediation:
Change the login endpoint to POST and read credentials from the request body over HTTPS:

app.post('/login', express.json(), (req, res) => {
  const { username, password } = req.body;
  ...
});

Additionally terminate TLS at the application or a reverse proxy layer.

Remove credential data from log output entirely. Log only a non-sensitive identifier such as the username (never the password) and omit it from the SQL string representation:

console.log('Login attempt for user:', username);
// Never log the query string when it contains user-supplied credentials.

